\begin_layout Subsubsection
FCF
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
EV_{t}=\frac{FCF_{t+1}}{WACC-g}=\frac{(1+g)FCF_{t}}{WACC-g}\Rightarrow\frac{EV_{t}}{FCF_{t}}=\frac{1+g}{WACC-g}
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
FCF is the true source of value, but using it has some drawbacks.
 It assumes a particular growth rate, same for different companies.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The CF might be negative and is not readily available.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection
NOPAT
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\frac{EV_{t}}{NOPAT_{t}}=\frac{(1-RR)(1+g)}{WACC-g}
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
This multiple is much easier to calculate.
 A representative NOPAT requires acyclical investments and assumptions regarding
 the depreciation and forward tax benefits.
\end_layout

